getObject

public CwObject getObject(String id,
                          String type,
                          com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean readOnly,
                          com.conceptwave.scripting.Object expirationInterval,
                          com.conceptwave.scripting.Object metadataFinder)
Gets the interface data object from the cache. If the object is not in the cache the cache will call its loader script to get the object from external source. Depending on the readOnly flag the object which is brought into the cache memory will be made immutable.

Parameters:
id - The object id (string)
type - The object search type (string). The search type "cw$ORD" is reserved type for reading the orders by id from the database. The type "cw$BKT" reads the baskets by id from the database. For these two predefined search types the cache uses its own built-in loaders. The cache checks if the search type is a valid metadata name and if it is name of a document mapped to the database, order or finder with get operation it uses the built-in loader to load these objects. Please do not use dot character in the user defined search types which need to use the cache loader(s).
readOnly - If true the object in the memory is made immutable. Note that this will happen only if the object does not exists in the cache and is brought into the memory from its external source. If the object is found in the memory its read-only status is not changed. If it is read-write object it will stay read-write object.
expirationInterval - Can be number which specifies the expiration interval in seconds starting from the current time or Date parameter which specifies when the object should expire. Note that this will taken in account only if the object does not exists in the cache and is brought into the memory from its external source. If the object exists in the memory its expiration time is not changed. The expiration time is taken in account for the objects loaded with the built-in loaders as well as when the user loader does not set the expiration time (in which case the object never expires). If the user loader set the expiration time this parameter is ignored.
metadataFinder - Full metadata name of a metadata finder or metadata finder object. Used as additional way to find documents which are not mapped to database
Returns:
The requested object or null if the object is not in the memory and the cannot be found in the external source.

putObject

public void putObject(String id,
                      String type,
                      CwObject obj,
                      com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean readOnly,
                      com.conceptwave.scripting.Object expirationInterval)
Puts the given interface data object in the cache under the specified name and type. Sets the interface data object read-only status depending on the readOnly flag. If the object is set as read-only any attempt to modify it will throw exception.

Parameters:
id - The object id
type - The object type
obj - The interface object
readOnly - If true the object is made immutable (read-only)
expirationInterval - Can be number which specifies the expiration interval in seconds starting from the current time or Date parameter which specifies when the object should expire
